data.description: $10,000 towards rate buy down with an acceptable offer!  Motivated Seller!!  Recently reduced and now offering a rate buy down incentive!!!  Looking for privacy and recreation all in one?  Look no further!  This home and acreage provides everything for off the grid living, if you choose!  Welcome to 374 Driftwood Road! Paradise awaits at this magnificent property, offering a spacious 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom home spanning over 2,500 square feet. Situated on a vast 17+ acre parcel just a stone's throw from Lake Greenwood, this home provides easy access to the lake's nearby public park. The property is a haven of tranquility, surrounded by lush woods and boasting total privacy. Outdoor enthusiasts will be thrilled by the numerous opportunities it presents, including hunting, riding, hiking trails, camping, fruit tree cultivation, and space for gardening and livestock. The house itself is versatile, with two primary suites and an open split floor plan. Upon entering, you'll be captivated by the generously sized living area, perfect for gatherings. The kitchen is a chef's dream, featuring modern appliances, ample counters, and a convenient breakfast bar.  The primary suite offers a true oasis of relaxation, complete with a private ensuite bathroom featuring a separate shower and an exceptionally large walk-in closet. Three additional bedrooms provide ample space for family members or guests. Step outside onto the deck and soak in the serene views of the surrounding landscape. With nearly 18 acres at your disposal, the possibilities are endless, whether you're interested in gardening, outdoor recreation, or simply enjoying the tranquility of your private paradise. Moreover, this home is conveniently located just a short 20-minute drive from Greenwood, Laurens, and Clinton, with numerous excellent restaurants and amenities within a 5-minute drive.
